CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1952, pg. 11, reads: "Bride - Mary Jane Harris, daughter of Mrs. Maude Harris, became the bride of Hubert Moton March in a charming home ceremony. Given away by her brother, the bride was a lovely picture as she repeated her vows.  Attendants were Helen Steward and Lornell Davis. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, including groom Hubert Moton, and five women, including bride Mary Jane Harris Moton wearing sheer fingerless gloves, posed in home
